Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(627.2,450.8)}Ten: Tenho-doori no Kaidanji\N(The Nice Guy on Tenho Way)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.46,0:03:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.37,0:03:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,With that Pon call and the new draw order, the game flow changed instantly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.43,0:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Again the 7 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.92,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What a terrifying draw
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably Akagi's winning tile
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Either the 4 Pin or this 7 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I discard either...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His only choice is to break up a hidden triplet
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.00,0:04:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he's back to square one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.12,0:05:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.52,0:05:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if only the game flow would come
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,With that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.35,0:05:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,could even Akagi lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.03,0:06:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt Akagi's game flow has moved to Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.46,0:06:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah.\NI can't hold him off forever with this hand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one, two turns maybe\N but that's probably the limit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Discard the 3 Pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's discarding only safe tiles he should choose the 6 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But he won't do that after coming so far
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.10,0:06:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you discard, Ten?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy discarded a 6 Pin before
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And despite it being a dangerous tile...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.57,0:06:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he wasn't nervous at all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to say he theorized it was safe
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a... WALL.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:55.86,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(615.618,128.823)}Wall: (壁 Kabe) A defensive strategy based on the unavailability of certain tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A 3/6 Pin wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:07:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, this guy knows the location of at least three of the 4 Pin or 5 Pin tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one 4 Pin out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy has either two 4 Pin or three 5 Pin tiles in his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.55,0:07:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what's he waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's likely with two 4 Pin tiles he'll aim for an Iipeikou
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:26.35,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(624.001,167.778)}Iipeikou: A hand with one set of two sequences of the same numbers in the same suit. (here: 2Pin-2Pin-3Pin-3Pin-4Pin-4Pin)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If he gets a 4 Pin he'd be waiting for a 3 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.83,0:07:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.43,0:07:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tanyao. 4 Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:51.92,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(619.937,73.459)}Tanyao: Hand composed number tiles 2-8.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.89,0:07:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,8,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.57,0:07:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Three 7 Man tiles, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.09,0:08:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You catch on well.\NA fine read
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.20,0:08:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good discards.\NDiscards that show intention
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.15,0:08:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The consecutive Red Dragon discards, and discarding the Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.40,0:08:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,With this are you going to close the 9,500 point gap in the final hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.77,0:08:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got some fighting spirit, don't you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If I play sluggishly I'll be dead
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it seems like the wind is changing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.12,0:08:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As I suspected.\NAkagi's next draw was a 7 Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.15,0:08:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He would have won on his next draw
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:45.76,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,South Hand 4\N Last Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The points still stand at Akagi 37,000 and Ten 27,500
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.00,0:08:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Point difference: 9,500
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.89,0:09:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,His starting hand is bad
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.97,0:09:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But for Ten to pull off an upset...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.63,0:09:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he must get at least 5,200 points this hand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.63,0:09:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.40,0:09:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no. For no reason they're completing their hands fast
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.35,0:09:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a dangerous.\N He skillfully passed it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.80,0:09:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.49,0:09:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is another dangerous tile
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.72,0:10:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec.\NAkagi's doing that on purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.92,0:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.92,0:10:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If the other guys win, Ten can't take the top spot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.89,0:10:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi will throw this hand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.89,0:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he deal into one of their hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's aiming for a White Dragon ToiToi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:19.64,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(643.555,80.667)}ToiToi: Hand composed of all triplets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If he wins that's 5,200 points
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.09,0:10:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But, what to do about the dora?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If Akagi miscalculates and that guy has Dora, it could drastically change the scoring
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's even the chance of a Dora Makura*
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:31.60,Default - top - cyan,,0,0,0,,Makura: (枕) Antique term for the single pair in a completed hand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.46,0:10:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one Dora in the discards
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.20,0:10:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Akagi holding the remaining 3 Dora tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.95,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In this particular hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have zero need to dwell on winning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can't do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.52,0:10:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have someone else tell me what to discard
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.92,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As I expected. This dummy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no.\NIf Akagi deals into that guy's hand, it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.66,0:11:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,White dragon ToiToi.\N5,200 points
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck.\NThis is what Akagi was aiming for
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.40,0:11:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've won this East South game
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.63,0:11:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And.. how is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.20,0:11:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:12:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I ALSO on that discard...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,RON YOU
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.69,0:12:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinhu, Iipeikou.\N2,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.70,0:12:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,2,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.70,0:12:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but that isn't an upset
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No. But look at the points
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shanyu? (Playoff round)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:30.88,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(634.444,128.445)}shānyū: (西入, entering the West). An extended West round when no player exceeds 30,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.17,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly top rated Akagi dealt 5,200 points into that guy's hand
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and with Ten winning 2,000 points, he's at 29,500
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has reached 30,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd expect as much from a Kantō ringer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:45.03,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(635.778,73.999)}Kantō: The greater Tokyo area in western Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well judged
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.86,0:12:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.35,0:12:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If my points in this extended round come beneath Ten's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.93,0:13:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll forfeit the match
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.12,0:13:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,W-what are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.12,0:13:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At best you'll be helping him
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He's baiting you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.83,0:13:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand at all
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That which we're trading...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.26,0:13:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't POINTS
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.72,0:13:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's PRIDE
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:30.31,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,West Hand 1
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.43,0:13:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,2,000 points from everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That last moment double Ron in the previous game...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It changed the game flow
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.95,0:13:49.48,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,West Hand 1\NFirst Honba.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.40,0:13:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.90,0:13:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,WHOOP THERE IT IS
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:13:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,4,100 points from everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:02.21,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,West Hand 3
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.29,0:14:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.16,0:14:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,8,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.78,0:14:17.78,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,West Hand 4\NFinal hand
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All things considered, Ten should come top this round
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.69,0:14:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If Akagi can't win with a Yakuman hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.83,0:14:30.71,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(631.111,125.111)}Yakuman:  The rarest and most valuable hands. 48,000/32,000 points for dealer/non-dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.12,0:14:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't pull of an upset
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.46,0:14:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In the worst case Ten can play safe discards
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.40,0:14:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just glimpse victory
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,From the first the possibility of DaiSanGen disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:55.90,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(608,128.667)}DaiSanGen, Kokusi Musou, Shousuushi etc. are all Yakuman valued hands
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.26,0:14:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that the chance of Kokusi Musou is gone too
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.09,0:15:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.56,0:15:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now shousuushii, daisuushii, and tsuuiisou are gone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.83,0:15:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.60,0:15:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And now even ryuuiisou is gone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.06,0:15:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.17,0:15:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With that nearly every chance at a Yakuman hand is gone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.37,0:15:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are going ideally
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.23,0:16:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No...\NThere's one avenue remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.83,0:16:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's going to pull an upset, It can be nothing else
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.96,0:16:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.96,0:17:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi has a single wait SuuAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.96,0:17:02.33,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(606.222,68.222)}SuuAnKou: 4 Hidden triplets
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.53,0:17:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But... what is he waiting on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.66,0:17:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Drawing an East Wind right after Akagi declares Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tough to discard it considering the game flow, but Ten's 4 Sou triplet is also difficult to discard...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.83,0:18:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're saved
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten has all four in his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.40,0:18:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 100% certain to not be Akagi's hidden-triple single wait tile
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.32,0:18:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten has all but won
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So. The 4 Man, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.55,0:19:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but that's not a SuuAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.15,0:19:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you haven't overtaken Ten's points!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.40,0:19:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.40,0:19:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.40,0:19:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a hidden triplet s over THERE
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.16,0:19:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,First, 3 Ura-dora.\NA Haneman hand
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.87,0:19:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and with this it's 6 Ura-Dora.\NA Baiman hand
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.87,0:19:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,T-that can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:19:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he pull such an upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.96,0:19:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If he turns over the same tile again, he'll have 9 Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:19:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,An indisputable MATHEMATICAL Yakuman
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.25,0:20:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.53,0:20:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.30,0:20:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If I placed lower than Ten in this Round
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:20:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'd forfeit the match
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.90,0:20:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-ou can't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.87,0:21:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo hoo!\NWE WON
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.40,0:21:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we celebrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.45,0:21:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.70,0:21:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't had such a hot blooded match...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.27,0:21:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long, long time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.99,0:21:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.83,0:21:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wanted to come back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.47,0:21:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,S-saved
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, 3 Ura-Dora?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's literally no chance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.60,0:21:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When Akagi got up to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.39,0:22:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't hear him, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.30,0:22:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It went as he expected
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The next tile over?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.82,0:22:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Next tile?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.73,0:22:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Akagi in his prime...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.60,0:22:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Would have turned over all 3
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.02,0:22:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This was Akagi Shigeru's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.42,0:22:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,SuuAnKou "Hell" wait
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.33,0:22:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mere chance gave me the win
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.30,0:22:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It could just as well have been him, maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.07,0:23:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten. Thanks for everything.\NYou saved me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.42,0:23:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me return the favor somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.50,0:23:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this ringer business already
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.30,0:23:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.30,0:23:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no problem with your Mahjong ability
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.13,0:23:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you play a little longer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.13,0:23:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and you lose your natural innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.73,0:23:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno, you just might be able to survive in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.59,0:23:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.59,0:23:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just stop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.02,0:23:42.33,Default - top,,0,0,0,,"Demons haunt the crossroads"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.33,0:23:45.22,Default - top,,0,0,0,,"Demons gather at the bones"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:49.19,Default - top,,0,0,0,,The bones are the tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.93,0:23:52.53,Default - top,,0,0,0,,In this underworld...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.53,0:23:56.39,Default - top,,0,0,0,,there are any number of evil, powerful, brilliant characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.39,0:24:00.25,Default - top,,0,0,0,,They gather at the tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.36,0:24:06.33,Default - top,,0,0,0,,The world you ought to be in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.33,0:24:08.33,Default - top,,0,0,0,,it ain't this one
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.53,0:24:14.05,Default - top,,0,0,0,,I entered this damn place more than once
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.05,0:24:16.05,Default - top,,0,0,0,,and for me it's too late. I can't go back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.33,0:24:21.33,Default - top,,0,0,0,,I have no choice but to live in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.70,0:24:24.16,Default - top,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.16,0:24:27.73,Default - top,,0,0,0,,you can still turn back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.10,0:24:33.66,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Later
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.95,0:24:59.75,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.56,0:24:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,An underground Mahjong East/West competition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.62,0:24:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle isn't the place for a normie like you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.47,0:24:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a Yakuza boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.47,0:24:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as being a ringer.\NHarada Katsumi
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.21,0:24:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This Mahjong is a scramble over life and death!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.24,0:25:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He's done the UNTHINKABLE.
